transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. This is Michelle. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hi, Michelle. This is Don Wiggum calling. How are you?

Speaker 1: Good. How you doing, Don?

Speaker 2: I'm doing fine.

Speaker 1: Sorry, I was trying to get off the phone because I saw you sitting in my list.

Speaker 2: Well, I figured you were on the phone, so I just held.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: But anyway, I want to pay you some money.

Speaker 1: Here's what happened. I didn't ever get the pills and—

Speaker 2: That you had told me you were sending, and then I finally got them.

Speaker 1: But anyway, I had one more day before I could deny the charge on my card.

Speaker 2: So just in case, I went ahead and denied the charge.

Speaker 1: And I saw that the credit card company told me that you guys refunded me all of it.

Speaker 2: So that's good.

Speaker 1: So the pills do work a little better than the first ones you sent me, the regular Sildenafil.

Speaker 2: So I want to pay you for that. I want to pay you for them.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: So what do I need to do? Just tell my credit card company that I want to pay for those?

Speaker 1: Yeah. Okay.

Speaker 2: So I see. So whenever someone calls their credit card company and disputes it—

Speaker 1: It's called a chargeback where we automatically...

Speaker 2: And then our company blacklists you from ever buying from us again because it hurts our business.

Speaker 1: But I'm going to have...

Speaker 2: Oh, okay. Okay.

Speaker 1: Yeah. Yeah. It's just automatic.

Speaker 2: But I'm going to have the IT guy go ahead and remove yours.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Yeah, because it's just bad for our business when people call the bank before calling us.

Speaker 1: Yeah. I hadn't...

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: But I had one day left.

Speaker 2: No, it's totally fine.

Speaker 1: I had one day left to dispute the charge.

Speaker 2: And it had been 60 days and y'all sent me the wrong thing.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: And then I returned the others.

Speaker 1: And then they sent me the wrong thing.

Speaker 2: I never knew if I was going to get credit or not.

Speaker 1: I never knew if I was going to get credit or not.

Speaker 2: So I figured...

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: And I wrote them and told them.

Speaker 1: I said, they've been very cooperative.

Speaker 2: The customer support has been very cooperative.

Speaker 1: However, I've got one more day to dispute the charge.

Speaker 2: So just in case...

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: I don't blame you.

Speaker 1: I would do anything.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: I'm not doing it.

Speaker 2: But anyway, I owe you for the pills that you sent.

Speaker 1: Okay. Well, hold on one second.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: I'm going to...

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: I just messaged the IT guy to remove your thing.

Speaker 2: So can I give you a call back in like 10 minutes?

Speaker 1: And instead of just giving me money, I'll just send you another 10.

Speaker 2: Another 10?

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: I'm not just going to take your money without...

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: No.

Speaker 1: So, yeah.

Speaker 2: If you pay, then I'll just send you just a refill.

Speaker 1: No, I hadn't paid.

Speaker 2: I hadn't paid.

Speaker 1: Right now, they've zeroed everything because y'all issued a credit.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: So...

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Let me see if I can do the charge.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: So, what I was asking, since y'all sent me the wrong thing and I hadn't spent so much time—

Speaker 2: How about I just pay the $64 and something?

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: $63.95?

Speaker 1: Whatever it was.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Is that good?

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: That's perfect.

Speaker 2: Give me one second.

Speaker 1: You're too sweet.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: And that way, we'll remove your blacklist in case you ever need a refill.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: I've already recommended them to a buddy of mine and...

Speaker 1: Awesome.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: I told him they work a little bit better.

Speaker 2: I said, it's not miraculous.

Speaker 1: But you had also told me something about if it didn't work as effectively as I thought...

Speaker 2: Oh, the activator.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: You'd recommend something else.

Speaker 1: What?

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: So, we have...

Speaker 1: Amino acid.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: It's the amino acid supplement.

Speaker 2: And what you do, you take two before you go to bed every night for about seven days in a row.

Speaker 1: And what it does, it kind of reboots your systems and increases your blood flow and your oxygen levels.

Speaker 2: But you don't take the activator with the AGB.

Speaker 1: You take the activator for like seven days in a row and then take the AGB after the seventh day.

Speaker 2: Now, what is that?

Speaker 1: Nitrates or something?

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: It's amino acid nitric oxide production.

Speaker 2: Nitric oxide.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: It's got L-carnitine, L-citrulline, L-arginine.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: That's pretty much it.

Speaker 2: Do you want me to send you that?

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: How much is it?

Speaker 1: No.

Speaker 2: I can send it to you for free.

Speaker 1: But the only thing is you would have to go back on the automatic refills.

Speaker 2: But what we can do is we can pause you for six months.

Speaker 1: That way it keeps your profile open and just allows you to call in whenever you need a refill.

Speaker 2: I can pause that until July 31st.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: That sounds good.

Speaker 2: And then I'll call my credit card company and explain it.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Perfect.

Speaker 1: And tell them to charge me the $63.95.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Perfect.

Speaker 2: I'll do that.

Speaker 1: And then I'll give you a call back, too, because I've got to go talk to the IT guy.

Speaker 2: Oh, okay.

Speaker 1: Well, no big deal.

Speaker 2: You can call me tomorrow if you're busy.

Speaker 1: It's no big deal.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: It's kind of slow today.

Speaker 2: I'll get it done today.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Well, you're a nice lady and I appreciate it.

Speaker 1: No problem.

Speaker 2: I'm glad I can help you.

Speaker 1: Did you say Don or do you go by William?

Speaker 2: Don?

Speaker 1: Well, Don, but all my partners list it as William.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Perfect, Don.

Speaker 2: I'll give you a call back in like 15 minutes or so.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Sounds great.

Speaker 1: Thanks.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: No problem.

Speaker 2: Bye.
